<b><h1>FOOD IN MYSORE</h1></b>

<p>Mysore is home to delicious and unique foods that you may not find anywere else.The city is a paradise for 
vegetarians, but not without an exception- especially if you get curious to try Coorg cuisine,
which is well represented in Mysore.Here are a few places you should definitely try!</p>

<div class="right">
<b><h2>Vinayaka Mylari</h2></b><br>
<p>This no-nonsense place is one of the best eateries in town
  to try South Indian classics of masala dosa and beautifully light and fluffy and idlis.Locals
   eat them with coconut chutney and a coffee.</p></div>
<div class="left"> 
<a href="https://www.zomato.com/mysore/vinayaka-mylari-doora">
<img src="idli.jpg" height="200" width="300"></a></div>

<div class="right">
<b><h2>Malgudi Café</h2></b><br>
<p>Set around an inner courtyard within the Green Hotel,
 this cafe brews excellent coffees and Himalayan teas to be enjoyed with
  excellent homemade cakes (lemon drizzle is great!) and sandwiches.
   Staff come from underprivileged backgrounds and are all women,
    and profits assist disadvantaged communities.</p>
</div>
<div class="left"> 
<img src="malgudi.jpg" height="200" width="300"></div>


<div class="right">
<b><h2>Cafe Aramane</h2> </b>
<p>In a character filled heritage building,this typically busy South Indian
eatery rolls out steaming breakfast platters for Mysuru's office goers, 
thalis for lunch(from Rs.80) and welcomes them back in the evenings with aromatic filter coffee and
 delicious snacks.
 There are speciality dosas each day of the week.</p>   
</div>
<div class="left"> 
<a href="www.zomato.com/mysore/aramane-cafe-chamrajpura">
<img src="filterkaapi.jpg" height="200" width="300"></a>
</div>



<div class="right">
<b><h2>Old House</h2></b><br>
<p>Classy Italian with delightful terrace for tasty salads, pasta and risotto and pizzas
 (baked in a wood-fired oven). 
They serve a full range of mocktails and coffees but no alcohol.</p></div>
<div class="left">
<a href="www.zomato.com/mysore/the-old-house-chamrajpura">
<img src="the-old-house.jpg" height="200" width="300"></a></div>



<div class="right">
<b><h2>Anu's Bamboo Hut</h2></b><br>
<p>Rooftop shack cafe catering mainly to yoga students with healthy vegetarian lunch buffets (from 1pm) 
and evening smoothies.
 Chef-owner Anu is a great source of info and offers cooking classes (Rs.700, lunch included).</p>
